Title : Felsenberg-Berntal Nature Reserve
Text : [[File:Berntal.jpg|thumb|Berntal, view from the hill of Herxheimer Felsenberg]]
The '''Felsenberg-Berntal Nature Reserve''' ({{lang-de|Naturschutzgebiet Felsenberg-Berntal}}), is an outlier of the [[Haardt mountains]], which form the eastern ridge of the [[Palatine Forest]] region in western [[Germany]]. The [[Nature reserves of Germany|nature reserve]], which extends into the [[Upper Rhine Plain]] and has an area of 300&nbsp;hectares, was established in January 2000 by a statute dated 20 December 1999.<ref name="vo-1999">{{cite web|author=[[Landkreis Bad Dürkheim]] |title=Rechtsverordnung über das Naturschutzgebiet „Felsenberg-Berntal“ |url=http://www.naturschutz.rlp.de/Dokumente/rvo/nsg/332203.htm |date=1999-12-20 |access-date=2011-12-07 }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The reserve lies in the county of [[Landkreis Bad Durkheim|Bad Durkheim]] in the German state of [[Rhineland-Palatinate]] and comprises the ''Felsenberg'' hill and the ''Berntal'' valley. The Herxheim Karst Cave on one of its hillsides is known for its archaeological and biological finds.

